<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12021i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12021i">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12021i"> 21(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Delaney (Delauney)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Nicolas Delaunay est po&egrave;te &agrave; ses heures; il adore les l&eacute;gendes, o&ugrave; rayonne Madame Marie et o&ugrave; Messire Satanas montre ses cornes. Aussi, le moine vous conduit-il aupr&egrave;s d&apos;un gros bloc de pierre: &ldquo;Voyez-vous cette empreinte?&raquo;, vous demandera-t-il. Par politesse, vous dites: &ldquo;Oui&raquo;. La v&eacute;rit&eacute; est que vous ne distinguez pas tr&egrave;s bien. Alors le bon prieur vous affirmera, sans rire, que c&apos;est la griffe du Diable poursuivi par l&apos;Archange. Celui-ci force celui-l&agrave; &agrave; se r&eacute;fugier en Bretagne, son pays de pr&eacute;dilection, assure un chroniqueur du temps qui, &agrave; n&apos;en pas douter, &eacute;tait normand. Si vous d&eacute;clarez, tout net, au prieur que l&apos;empreinte n&apos;est pas celle d&apos;un pied fourchu, il vous r&eacute;pondra, qu&apos;apr&egrave;s tout, c&apos;est peut-&ecirc;tre le pied de l&apos;Archange&hellip; <br:<font color="green">[Nicolas Delaunay is a poet at times; he adores the legends where Madame Marie shines and Messire Satanas shows his horns. The monk will lead you to a great stone block. &ldquo;Do you seen this imprint?&rdquo; he will ask you. Politely, you will say: &ldquo;Yes.&rdquo; The truth is that you don&apos;t quite see it. Then the good prior will declare, without a smile, that this is a trace of the Devil chased away by the Archangel. The latter forced the former to hide in Brittany, his favourite land, claims the chronicler at the time, who was undoubtedly Norman. If you tell the prior that the print is not that of a hoofed foot, he will say that after all it might have been the foot of the Archangel.]</font> <small> &Eacute;tienne Dupont, <a name="LMSM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LMSM"><cite title="source">Les l&eacute;gendes du Mont-Saint-Michel</cite></a> (1924) 144</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Fr. Favourite country. </mm> </dd></dl>
